title: Egyptian Court Sentences Ousted President Morsi to Death
description: Mr. Morsi was sentenced to death over his part in a mass prison break that took place during the 2011 uprising that toppled Hosni Mubarak.

title: Court Sentences Egypt's Ousted President to Death
description: An Egyptian court has sentenced ousted President Mohammed Morsi to death.

title: Fair Game: Shareholders’ Votes Have Done Little to Curb Lavish Executive Pay
description: Despite rules empowering shareholders to rein in soaring pay packages, few have chosen to do so, perhaps because of a rising stock market.

title: For the Highest-Paid C.E.O.s, the Party Goes On
description: Four chief executives at five companies with ties to John C. Malone, who built a cable and communications empire, were awarded more than $350 million last year.

title: They Built It. No One Came.
description: In Pennsylvania, two men with 63 acres and a communal vision of utopia learn the hard way that not everyone follows the leader.

title: Russian Rocket Carrying Mexican Satellite Is Said to Crash in Siberia
description: The Proton-M rocket, which was ferrying a telecommunications satellite, crashed minutes after launch on Saturday, Russian news agencies reported.

title: 8 Bodies Recovered From Wreckage of Marine Helicopter, Nepal Army Says
description: Six Marines and two Nepali soldiers were aboard the UH-1 Huey that crashed Tuesday while assisting in earthquake relief efforts.

title: Clintons Earned $30 Million in 16 Months, Report Shows
description: The couple’s earnings and assets were to be detailed in disclosure forms that presidential candidates were required to file with federal officials.

title: Victims Find Solace and Sorrow in Boston Verdict and Are Ready to Move On
description: Victims and emergency medical workers reacted online and off to the jury decision that Dzhokhar Tsarnaev should get the death penalty for the 2013 attack.

title: F. A. O. Schwarz to Close Its Doors on Fifth Avenue
description: F.A.O. Schwarz, which has been a fixture in New York for 145 years and a character in the 1988 Tom Hanks film “Big,” is actively scouring Manhattan for a new, less costly location.

title: Amtrak Train Possibly Hit Before Wreck
description: An assistant conductor on the Amtrak train said she heard the engineer tell another operator in a radio transmission that the train had just been struck by something.

title: Dzhokhar Tsarnaev Given Death Penalty in Boston Marathon Bombing
description: The federal jury that convicted Mr. Tsarnaev last month in the Boston Marathon bombing rejected the defense’s case that his brother, Tamerlan, had held a malevolent sway over him and had led him to commit the crimes.

title: Racist Police Emails Put Florida Cases in Doubt
description: The state attorney’s office is looking into cases by two police officers in Miami Beach who exchanged about 230 emails containing racist and sexist jokes.

title: Washington Governor Declares Drought Emergency
description: Gov. Jay Inslee also warned that residents should be prepared for an active fire season.

title: Wreck Adds to the Debate on Amtrak Funding
description: Days after the deadly train derailment in Philadelphia, the debate over Amtrak funding continues to be a partisan flash point in Congress.

title: Obama Salutes Fallen Law Enforcement Officers as Heroes
description: The president spoke at a memorial ceremony to thousands of officers and family members of those killed in action.

title: 2 New York City Jail Employees Arrested on Smuggling Charges
description: Months after Mayor Bill de Blasio announced a crackdown on contraband smuggling at Rikers Island, employees continue to flout the law, investigators say.

title: 2 Women Moved to Write Stories Uncover a Surprisingly Personal One
description: Through a series of coincidences, two sisters adopted by different families more than 30 years ago find each other in a Columbia University classroom.

title: News Analysis: A Diplomatic Victory, and Affirmation, for Putin
description: A visit by Secretary of State John Kerry was seen as an olive branch and an acknowledgment that Russia is too important to ignore.

title: Charged With Graft in China, Some Fugitives Are Finding Luxury in U.S.
description: The United States, Canada, New Zealand and Australia, none of which have extradition treaties with China, were identified as the leading destinations for suspects.
